IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: The mission of west cap is to take action against poverty.
IRS990.MissionDescription: The mission of west cap is to take action against poverty by developing the social and economic assets of low-income families and their communities and by working to create a more just and sustainable society.
IRS990.Description: WEATHERIZATION/ENERGY PROGRAMS - Provide Residential Rehabilitation and energy conservation services to low income households to reduce utility bills and enhance community sustainability by using fewer resources. During the year, 1,031 participants received services through this program.

Activity2.Description: Housing - to provide affordable housing as well as emergency and housing assistance to low income individuals. Assistance services include: homebuyer, rental, security deposit, utility, mortgage foreclosure intervention, and housing counseling. During the year, 3,601 participants received services through this program.

Activity3.Description: FOOD services - to provide food security services to low income individuals. During the year, 935 participants received services through this program.

ActivityOther.Description: other programs - to provide services to low income participants in the west central wisconsin region.
community services - to provide community services to low income individuals

TRANSPORTATION - Provide transportation services to low income participants in the west central wisconsin region by assisting eligible families in buying reliable cars for work or employment training.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 11
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The finance committee reviews in detail the 990 and reports to the full board with a copy of the return given to each board member. The full board then approves the return to be filed.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 12c
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: conflict of interest disclosure forms are annually distributed to members of the board to re-sign or for new members to sign at new board member orientation. If there are conflicts the committee will review and make decisions.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 15
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: Triannually the organization reviews all staff compensation by conducting a market salary survey primarily with other community action agencies. The organization has also conducted independent salary research through the jobnet, guidestar, and other salary websites, or by contacting organizations that do similar type of work. The organization's board of directors approves all compensation changes for the executive director position.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, line 19
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The organization does not make its governing documents, conflict of interest policy, or financial statements available to the public.

The Board of Directors assumes responsibility for oversight of the audit. Selection of an independent accountant is determined by sealed bid process. Responses are reviewed and ranked by the Finance Director based on the bid documentation - with qualifications being done before costs are ranked. Executive Director and Finance Director then review scoring and agree on award recipient.
